physical_appearance: This is a photograph of the Shwedagon Pagoda in Rangoon, Burma. The photograph shows the entrance to the Pagoda, with steps leading up to the Stupa. There is a decorated archway at the top of the steps. At the bottom-left, there is a horse-drawn carriage driven by a man. On the bottom-right, there are several people sitting on the ground. There are also a few people on the steps to the Pagoda. The title is written at the bottom, below the photograph. The top-right corner of the photograph is folded inwards.
title_text: Photograph album of views and portraits in the Punjab, Cashmere, Ceylon, Burma, Penang, Singapore, and Java Upper entrance of Shwedagon Pagoda, Rangoon
